Reasoning: 
1. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses static binary search trees and their runtime analysis, which falls under the scope of data structures and algorithms. 
2. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper mentions entropy and its relation to the runtime of the classic root-finger tree, which is a concept from information theory. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses dynamic programming to compute the optimal tree, which is a technique commonly used in machine learning. 
4. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper involves mathematical analysis of the runtime of the lazy finger tree, which is a topic in discrete mathematics. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - The paper discusses the runtime analysis of different search methods in binary search trees, which is a topic in computational complexity.
